{
  "texts": [
    "[123] take a different route to the established multi-modal approach and instead use different forms of visual information.",
    "Li et al. [122] take inspiration from [39] and make use of both semantic and spatial graphs to represent the image.",
    "In addition to these explicit graphs, they also introduce an implicit graph, i.e.",
    "a fully connected graph between the detected objects with edge weights set by a GAT.",
    "The relation-aware visual features are then combined with the question vector using multi-modal fusion."
  ]
}